      "contents": [
        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"adaptation_kind\":\"Restructure\",\"safety_tier\":\"Green\",\"nudge_patch\":null,\"restructure_plan\":{\"revised_weekly_targets\":[{\"week_number\":1,\"weekly_target_km\":30},{\"week_number\":2,\"weekly_target_km\":36},{\"week_number\":3,\"weekly_target_km\":40}],\"revised_current_week_workouts\":[{\"day_of_week\":1,\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"title\":\"Easy Aerobic Run\",\"target_distance_km\":7,\"target_duration_minutes\":42,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":360,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":360,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Start very relaxed, let the body wake up gradually.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":32,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Comfortable conversational effort throughout. If legs still feel heavy, back off a touch — the pace is a guide, not a ceiling.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Walk or very slow jog to close.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"5 minutes easy walking or very light jogging before you settle into pace.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"5 minutes easy walking, gentle quad and calf stretches.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Monday's easy run is unchanged — it was completed and serves as the aerobic foundation for the week. Keep effort genuinely easy; you should be able to hold a full conversation.\",\"perceived_effort\":4},{\"day_of_week\":3,\"workout_type\":\"Tempo\",\"title\":\"Controlled Threshold Run\",\"target_distance_km\":6,\"target_duration_minutes\":30,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":360,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":285,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":8,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Easy jog to raise heart rate gently before threshold work.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":16,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":285,\"intensity\":\"Threshold\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Comfortably hard — controlled and sustainable. If pace slips beyond 295 s/km, ease back rather than forcing it.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":6,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Easy jog back to full recovery.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"8-minute easy jog; include 2–3 light strides at the end if you feel ready.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"6-minute easy jog followed by calf, hamstring, and hip flexor stretches.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Wednesday's tempo is trimmed from 8 km to 6 km to give your legs room to deliver quality effort at the prescribed Daniels-Gilbert threshold zone rather than grinding through a longer session at reduced intensity. Quality over quantity this week.\",\"perceived_effort\":7},{\"day_of_week\":5,\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"title\":\"Easy Recovery Run\",\"target_distance_km\":5,\"target_duration_minutes\":30,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":360,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":360,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":3,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Start very gently.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":24,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Fully conversational pace. Think of this as active recovery — you are flushing fatigue, not adding fitness stress.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":3,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Ease to a walk for the final minute.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"3 minutes very easy jogging or brisk walking.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"3 minutes easy walking, light stretching.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Friday drops from 6 km to 5 km to reduce cumulative load and set up a better long run on Sunday. Pace should feel genuinely easy — slower is fine.\",\"perceived_effort\":3},{\"day_of_week\":0,\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"title\":\"Controlled Long Run\",\"target_distance_km\":12,\"target_duration_minutes\":72,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":360,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":360,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":8,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"First 8 minutes very easy to let legs loosen up.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":56,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Steady easy aerobic effort. If legs feel heavy again in the first 3 km, ease pace to 370–375 s/km — completing the distance at a slightly slower pace is more valuable than stopping early.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":8,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Final 8 minutes at a very relaxed shuffle, then walk it in.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"8-minute very easy jog; no strides today.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"8 minutes easy jog into a walk; spend 5–10 minutes on full-body stretching, prioritising glutes, calves, and hip flexors.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Sunday's long run is reduced from 14 km to 12 km. That's still a meaningful aerobic stimulus — comfortably the longest run of the week — while giving your legs the space they need to perform rather than survive. All of Sunday's running stays in the easy pace-zone index band.\",\"perceived_effort\":5}],\"forward_path\":\"This week lands at 30 km — a deliberate step back that lets your legs absorb and reset rather than compound the fatigue you've described. From there, Week 2 rebuilds to 36 km (roughly a 20% lift, which is intentionally a bit more assertive than normal only because Week 1 was pulled below baseline), and Week 3 returns to 40 km, which is where the original plan opened. You'll be back on the original progression curve by Week 3, and from there the build toward your sub-1:45 half continues with that solid aerobic base underneath you.\"},\"net_load_delta\":-10,\"rationale\":\"Cutting Sunday's long run short when your legs had no power in them was exactly the right call — pushing through that kind of heaviness rarely produces fitness and often produces injury. What the recent sessions show together is a body that's accumulating fatigue faster than it's recovering from it: the tempo drifted well outside the Daniels-Gilbert threshold band, Friday took longer than expected, and Sunday's legs simply weren't there. That's a clear signal, not a character flaw. Here's what I've changed: Wednesday's tempo is trimmed to 6 km so you can hit a genuine threshold effort rather than grinding a longer one at reduced intensity; Friday drops to 5 km to keep it truly easy; and Sunday's long run comes down to 12 km — still a real long run, just one your legs can actually run well rather than survive. The week lands at 30 km total. From there, Week 2 rebuilds to 36 km and Week 3 returns to 40 km, putting you right back on the original progression curve. Rest this week is the investment that makes the next 15 weeks possible.\",\"referral_category\":null}"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
